<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 24px;
        color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
      }
      table {
        max-width: 600px;
        padding: 0 12px 24px 12px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
      }
      tr {
        text-align: left;
      }
      hr {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      a {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:link {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:visited {
        color: #4c6259;
      }
      a:hover {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:active {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      .article-title {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .text-centered {
        text-align: center;
      }
      .pb-s {
        padding-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .pb-m {
        padding-bottom: 24px;
      }
      .pb-l {
        padding-bottom: 48px;
      }
      .pb-xl {
        padding-bottom: 56px;
      }
      .color-main {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .font-s {
        font-size: 12px;
      }
    </style>
    <title>AR Weekly</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <table class="text-centered">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-centered">
            <img
              src="<%= @logo_url %>"
              alt="AR Weekly"
              width="100px"
              height="100px"
            />
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-centered font-s pb-xl">
            Issue #<%= @issue_number %>, <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date, "{D} {Mfull} {YYYY}") %>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-xl">
            Hello guys! This digest covers Augmented Reality related news between <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date_from, "{D} {Mfull}") %> and <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date_to, "{D} {Mfull}") %>. Enjoy!
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Mobile AR Top 5 Games
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            Venturebeat released a top 5 list f√ºr mobile AR games. Although top x lists are always subjective and not all agree, they provide a handy overview of the current market. The following games made the list. Knightfall AR: an augmented reality experience that places you in the world of The Knights Templar, as they seek to defend the city of Acre. The Machines: transforms your table in a roboter battle PvP Arena. Temple Treasure Hunt: an indoor and outdoor treasure hunt. AR Smash Tanks!: a shoot'em up title similar to Worms. Harry Potter: Wizards Unite!: the successor of Pokemon Go from Niantic - a multiplayer location-based action game.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://venturebeat.com/2019/08/06/knights-tanks-and-wizards-ars-top-5-games")) %>'
              >https://venturebeat.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Google Maps AR Navigation Beta
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            From this week on, Google Maps will include a beta version of the AR navigation feature. The feature is designed for urban areas where GPS positioning might not always be accurate enough. The functionality will be available for compatible devices (AR Core / ARKit ready).
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://venturebeat.com/2019/08/08/google-maps-ar-navigation-launches-in-beta-for-compatible-ios-and-android-devices")) %>'
              >https://venturebeat.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Apple AR Glasses: To Be or Not To Be
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            AR Insider did a fact check on current rumours for the Apple AR glasses. While they think that the wearable device is still on Apple's roadmap, it just might not be for next year.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://arinsider.co/2019/08/07/triangulating-the-latest-evidence-for-apple-ar-glasses")) %>'
              >https://arinsider.co</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Consumer AR Revenues Projected to Reach $7.9 Billion by 2023
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            As always, ARtillry Intelligence is crunching data. This week they released an update on their projected consumer AR numbers.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://arinsider.co/2019/08/08/consumer-ar-revenues-projected-to-reach-7-9-billion-by-2023")) %>'
              >https://arinsider.co</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            Suggestions or comments are more than welcome! Just reply to this
            email.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-xl">
            Thanks for reading<br />
            <span class="color-main"><strong>AR</strong>&nbsp;Weekly</span>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m font-s">
            You receive this Email because you are subscribed to the AR Weekly
            Blog. Your next delivery is on <%= Timex.format!(@next_issue_date, "{D} {Mfull} {YYYY}") %>.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-s">
            <a href="<%= @unsubscribe_url %>">Unsubscribe</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
            |&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="<%= @privacy_url %>">Privacy Policy</a
            >&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="mailto:hello@ar-weekly.blog">hello@ar-weekly.blog</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/Domeee/ar-weekly">Source Code @ GitHub</a>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <img width="1px" height="1px" src="<%= @issue_tracking_url %>" alt="">
  </body>
</html>
